1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,960
Get revenge on Boss Noo.

2
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:35,800
PREVIOUS EPISODE

3
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:38,000
-Puna?
-Hurry up!

4
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:39,360
Hey, Chaiya!

5
00:02:39,440 --> 00:02:42,800
Stay hidden here. Don't go anywhere.
I'll be back.

6
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:46,560
I saw Boss Noo around here.

7
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:51,760
-Are you okay, Boss?
-I'm fine!

8
00:02:57,560 --> 00:03:00,560
If the police hadn't arrived in time,
I'd have been the shooter.

9
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:04,160
Don't worry about the message
you sent to Corporal Chom.

10
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,200
He won't be able to trace us.

11
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:10,040
The number I'm using is encrypted by HQ,

12
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,880
so it can't be traced back to us.

13
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:20,200
Puna.

14
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:22,600
Who exactly are you guys?

15
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:30,320
Well, I'm Chaiya.

16
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:34,360
And I'm Manat. We still need
to get the clothes from the office.

17
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:39,320
I heard everything you guys said.

18
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:51,400
Alright.

19
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:56,080
I'll tell you the truth.

20
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:02,040
Go on.

21
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,560
I used to be a food delivery rider.

22
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,000
In high school,

23
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:08,680
I was also a boxer.

24
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:11,040
That's right. I met Chaiya
at the boxing gym.

25
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,480
Then we started making YouTube videos.

26
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,360
We're actually police.

27
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,880
Don't worry.

28
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:08,480
Sergeant Au is on our side.
We work together.

29
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:13,120
Yes.

30
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:15,520
The three of us

31
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:18,400
were sent to investigate
a drug case in Ban Khok Ta Yu.

32
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:25,240
How does that relate
to Singha's Darathong Music?

33
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:29,400
We found clues
that the label's executives

34
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:31,400
are involved in drug trafficking.

35
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:34,200
That's why we had to go undercover
and work at the company.

36
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:36,600
Maybe…

37
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:39,800
the reason my father and mother died

38
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,320
is connected to this too.

39
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:47,200
The car accident case

40
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,920
with Phupha Thararin
falling off the cliff?

41
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:51,760
You know about this too?

42
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:54,480
Of course. We're police.

43
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,600
We have to check everyone's backgrounds.

44
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:59,280
I have something to tell you too.

45
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:03,000
The reason I applied
to be a singer at this label

46
00:06:03,520 --> 00:06:06,360
is because I want to investigate
my parents' case as well.

47
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:11,720
Puna, we need to hurry back
and get the clothes.

48
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:14,760
Well, then.

49
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:18,480
You can tell us the details on the way.

50
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,240
Maybe we can help investigate as well.

51
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:24,080
Thanks.

52
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:25,120
Ahem.

53
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:26,440
Excuse me.

54
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:28,000
Will this take long?

55
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:29,920
The gas is running out.

56
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:33,000
-Please get in.
-Okay.

57
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:34,520
-Let's go.
-Well…

58
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:39,360
If you want to chat,
we can do it in the car.

59
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,600
Wow, even prepared for that.

60
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:56,240
DARATHONG MUSIC

61
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:57,360
Then,

62
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:01,840
the proof that will clear
your parents' names

63
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:04,000
is in that teddy bear?

64
00:07:05,080 --> 00:07:06,080
Yes.

65
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:08,680
Right now, that teddy bear
is in Singha's office,

66
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:11,120
but the opportunity hasn't come yet.

67
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,720
My mission isn't finished.

68
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:14,240
That's okay.

69
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:16,680
Manat and I will help.

70
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:19,600
If we get that evidence,

71
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:20,960
it'll help all of us too.

72
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:24,120
Thanks so much.

73
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:26,680
I promise I'll keep this a secret.

74
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,600
I won't tell anyone.

75
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:31,680
Thank you, Miss Puna.

76
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:33,880
This is life-or-death stuff.

77
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:36,320
If anyone else finds out, we're done for.

78
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:38,480
Thanks, Sergeant Au.

79
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,760
Yes, Captain.

80
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:45,360
Let's go. We should hurry
into the company.

81
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:56,240
SONRAK DARATHONG

82
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:58,480
Chaiya.

83
00:07:58,560 --> 00:07:59,720
Yes, Mr. Kitti.

84
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:00,960
Follow me.

85
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,440
So today's plan failed.

86
00:08:12,520 --> 00:08:13,720
The police got in the way.

87
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:24,960
Yes, Mr. Singha.

88
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:28,960
Chart called and reported
the same thing to me.

89
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:31,800
What about Boss Noo?
He's still alive, right?

90
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:32,799
Yes.

91
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:35,720
His men got him out in time.

92
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:38,280
The police shot him,
leaving him dragging his leg.

93
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:47,240
Boss Noo is in trouble now.

94
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:50,080
If we're dealing with him,
we have to act fast.

95
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,880
Or he'll come back for revenge.

96
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:54,960
Got it.

97
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:57,800
I'll check that Khod guy's family.

98
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:11,240
Let's go. The outfit's ready.

99
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:12,440
Got everything?

100
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:14,920
I've got the accessories too.
Nothing's missing.

101
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,200
Puna.

102
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:21,400
I found that teddy bear.

103
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:24,120
In Mr. Singha's office, right?

104
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,360
Yes.

105
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:29,520
Don't worry. I'll figure out
a way to help you.

106
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:37,160
I have to go.
Teacher Mueangphrai is calling.

107
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:38,840
Okay, see you later.

108
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:41,560
Yes, Teacher. I'm on my way.

109
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:53,120
DARATHONG MUSIC

110
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,360
Looks like something
really is hidden inside.

111
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:32,960
You've got an urgent schedule today.
You know that?

112
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:35,480
Yes, Dad. It's a product review, right?

113
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:38,800
Yes, the new products just came in.
Get them done quickly.

114
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:42,120
Have the products arrived?

115
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:44,040
Yes. Why, you haven't got them?

116
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:46,640
Not yet, Dad. Where are the products?

117
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:48,800
I saw it just now.

118
00:10:48,880 --> 00:10:49,880
Yes, Dad.

119
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:04,480
Hey, Khod. Your wife came to visit.

120
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,440
Khod.

121
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:11,080
Nok, how did you get here?

122
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:13,960
-He brought me.
-Who?

123
00:11:14,560 --> 00:11:15,760
It's me.

124
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:20,800
Too bad your kid
had to go to school today.

125
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:23,200
-What?
-Otherwise I'd have brought him too.

126
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:26,200
Don't do anything to my family! I beg you!

127
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:29,200
Don't worry. I won't hurt you.

128
00:11:30,560 --> 00:11:32,160
As long as you behave.

129
00:11:32,680 --> 00:11:34,080
What do you want me to do?

130
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:37,120
Just go back to Boss Noo

131
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:40,480
and send me the information
I need. That's all.

132
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:41,600
Easy.

133
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:46,640
Khod, do what he says.

134
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:49,160
He even sent someone
to watch our kid at school.

135
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:52,280
Uh…

136
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:55,360
Okay, I'll do it.

137
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:58,120
Whatever you want, I'll do it.

138
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:03,360
Oh, I'm so excited for you!

139
00:12:03,880 --> 00:12:05,320
Step down, yeah.

140
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:06,720
We're almost there!

141
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:07,720
-Oops!
-Oops!

142
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:10,480
Hey.

143
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:12,880
What's this surprise?
Why do I have to be blindfolded?

144
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:14,120
Alright, we're here.

145
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:16,640
One, two, three!

146
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:19,080
-Ta-da!
-Ta-da!

147
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:21,240
Whose car is this, Dad?

148
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:24,320
It's your car, my daughter.

149
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:26,360
Mine? Really mine?

150
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:31,240
Whoa!

151
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:34,720
You're already a singer on TV.

152
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:37,320
Riding a motorbike
in the sun and wind?

153
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:43,000
You deserve a brand-new car

154
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:44,880
to match your status

155
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:47,600
as a singer, my daughter.

156
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:50,760
Yay!

157
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:53,920
-Aw.
-I'm no ordinary dad.

158
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:56,800
Thank you so much, Dad!

159
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:58,080
You're the best!

160
00:12:58,160 --> 00:12:59,320
I'm no ordinary dad.

161
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:01,840
-The keys are with me.
-Alright.

162
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:03,960
Hand them over!

163
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:07,400
Here it is.

164
00:13:07,480 --> 00:13:08,560
-Here.
-Give them to her.

165
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:09,880
This is your car.

166
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:11,360
Wow.

167
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:17,240
-Yippee!
-I've got the keys!

168
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:20,680
Post it! We have to show it to the world!

169
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:22,920
Quick, Joey, take the shot!

170
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:23,880
Good idea!

171
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:25,680
Go ahead. Strike a pose!

172
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:26,760
-Strike a pose!
-Pose now?

173
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:28,840
-Alright, good. One…
-Make it look nice!

174
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:30,480
-So beautiful!
-Okay, I'm taking it.

175
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:31,640
-Yay.
-Okay.

176
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:40,400
Puna, did you know?

177
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:42,320
Maria just got a brand-new car.

178
00:13:47,280 --> 00:13:48,600
Great.

179
00:13:48,680 --> 00:13:52,200
Just her first song,
and she can already afford a car.

180
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:55,080
Maybe Village Head Prueng
bought it for her.

181
00:13:55,920 --> 00:13:59,000
He's ridiculously rich.

182
00:14:00,120 --> 00:14:01,280
But

183
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:04,120
she really shouldn't post it
for everyone to see.

184
00:14:06,120 --> 00:14:07,520
Forget it, Teacher.

185
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:10,360
That's their business.
Let's focus on our work.

186
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:15,960
DARATHONG MUSIC

187
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:17,760
Another box here!

188
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:20,960
Is it heavy, Ice?

189
00:14:21,040 --> 00:14:22,600
Not at all!

190
00:14:22,680 --> 00:14:26,280
These boxes are from fans
sending gifts to the artists.

191
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:30,160
The plushies
are for Mr. Sonrak and Maria.

192
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:32,560
There's a lot.

193
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:35,480
Looks like this ship couple trend
is really popular!

194
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:39,720
Is that all of them?

195
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:42,120
There's still a lot in the warehouse.

196
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:44,920
The team is bringing them in.

197
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,280
Enough already.

198
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:48,320
We can't even sort all of them.

199
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:50,400
Just a little more, Teacher.

200
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:53,200
-Can you help me carry them?
-Okay, let's go.

201
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:04,440
Puna.

202
00:15:07,640 --> 00:15:09,400
I just went into Singha's office.

203
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:12,000
You got the bear, right?

204
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:12,960
Not yet.

205
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:15,880
But I squeezed it and shook it a bit.

206
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,360
There has to be something inside.

207
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:29,040
Just hang on. I'll try another way.

208
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:36,600
And what are you doing here?

209
00:15:36,680 --> 00:15:39,080
These are fan gifts for the artists.

210
00:15:39,160 --> 00:15:41,040
We were instructed to donate them.

211
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:43,320
Donate to whom?

212
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:45,960
Kamnan Pong is giving them
to the kids and villagers.

213
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:50,120
But we have to sort them first,
then send some to the laundry

214
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:52,840
because some are old and dusty.

215
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:54,400
Alright, I'll help.

216
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:27,520
When you become a singer someday,

217
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:30,760
I'll be your first fan,
buying a plushie for you.

218
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:39,640
That's up to you.

219
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:42,680
Someone like you

220
00:16:42,760 --> 00:16:44,920
actually buys plushies for people?

221
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:48,000
Not really.

222
00:16:49,960 --> 00:16:51,480
But I'll buy it sincerely.

223
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:55,960
We'll see.

224
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:25,720
Chaiya, go prepare the car for me.

225
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:30,000
I've got a product review
this afternoon. Let's go.

226
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:32,840
Yes.

227
00:18:04,320 --> 00:18:06,880
Miss Maria! Hurry, hit the brakes!

228
00:18:10,120 --> 00:18:11,480
Brake!

229
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:16,280
Don't scream! You're scaring me.

230
00:18:16,360 --> 00:18:19,040
We're more scared! Be careful!

231
00:18:19,120 --> 00:18:20,280
Ah!

232
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:24,640
Miss Maria, take it slow.

233
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:27,560
A brand-new car?

234
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:29,120
Miss Maria.

235
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:31,400
Should I get out and guide you?

236
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:34,560
I'll get out too then.

237
00:18:35,360 --> 00:18:36,760
No need!

238
00:18:36,840 --> 00:18:39,800
We'll stay in the car.
If we crash, we crash together.

239
00:18:39,880 --> 00:18:42,320
-If we die, we die together.
-Ah!

240
00:18:45,640 --> 00:18:46,720
Oh no!

241
00:18:48,280 --> 00:18:49,320
What did you hit?

242
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,920
What is it?

243
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:53,920
Go check!

244
00:18:58,360 --> 00:18:59,200
Mr. Assistant!

245
00:18:59,280 --> 00:19:00,840
-Oh!
-Hey!

246
00:19:00,920 --> 00:19:03,680
Miss Maria ran over someone! Police!

247
00:19:03,760 --> 00:19:06,560
Why are you calling the police?
Call an ambulance!

248
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:08,600
Who do I call? Ambulance or police?

249
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:12,880
My legs are shaking.
Whoa, I'm about to pass out!

250
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:14,960
-Joey!
-Oh no!

251
00:19:15,040 --> 00:19:18,120
Hey, Manat! Hey!

252
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:19,680
Don't pass out on me.

253
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:22,960
Manat , I'm sorry! Are you okay?

254
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:25,960
Hey, stay with me. Wake up!

255
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:30,480
Tell the people at home for me…

256
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,080
Tell them what?

257
00:19:32,680 --> 00:19:33,840
Tell Mom…

258
00:19:33,920 --> 00:19:35,040
Tell what?

259
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:37,960
Tell her what?

260
00:19:39,360 --> 00:19:41,520
That I like you, Maria.

261
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:44,080
A dying person

262
00:19:44,920 --> 00:19:46,640
always tells the truth.

263
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:51,560
-You idiot!
-Ouch!

264
00:19:55,200 --> 00:19:57,040
That hurts, you know.

265
00:19:58,000 --> 00:19:59,680
-Are you messing with me?
-Hey!

266
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:01,360
Don't!

267
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,600
Wait, you weren't actually run over?

268
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:10,360
Today it's the cone,
next time, it could be something else.

269
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:13,360
If you can't reverse, call me.

270
00:20:14,360 --> 00:20:16,320
Don't interfere. Stay away!

271
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:17,640
Got it.

272
00:20:17,720 --> 00:20:19,360
I'm easygoing.

273
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:22,000
Anyone who becomes my girlfriend
will be very lucky.

274
00:20:22,080 --> 00:20:23,360
Very lucky?

275
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:28,720
-But today, let's make it bloody first!
-Hey!

276
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:29,880
Take that!

277
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:37,920
Stop smiling at me!

278
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:51,160
Miss Maria, why are you smiling?

279
00:20:58,520 --> 00:20:59,680
Hey!

280
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:02,080
Wake up!

281
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:04,960
You're overdoing it.

282
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:13,320
Puna.

283
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:15,000
Hand it over. I'll help.

284
00:21:15,080 --> 00:21:16,040
Thanks.

285
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:19,560
Put them in the van?

286
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:22,280
Yes. The van will take them
to the laundry.

287
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:31,520
This company is really kind.

288
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:32,560
Yeah.

289
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:34,200
Taking fan gifts

290
00:21:34,280 --> 00:21:37,040
and giving them to the kids like this
is really admirable.

291
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:39,200
But the important part

292
00:21:39,720 --> 00:21:42,720
is washing the plushies before donating.
I've never seen that before.

293
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:44,200
Exactly.

294
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:47,200
Normally, when I donate old things,
I never wash them.

295
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:49,000
This company does things right,

296
00:21:49,080 --> 00:21:50,960
thinking about the kids' health.

297
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:54,120
Some of them
have been stored for a long time.

298
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:56,360
They might have dust or germs.

299
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:58,320
That's why Mr. Singha insisted

300
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:01,120
they be cleaned before donation.

301
00:22:01,960 --> 00:22:03,320
Let me help.

302
00:22:10,080 --> 00:22:11,360
Time's up, Chaiya.

303
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:13,600
Stop talking now.

304
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:15,440
Yes.

305
00:22:15,520 --> 00:22:16,760
Manat too.

306
00:22:17,600 --> 00:22:18,680
He's slacking off.

307
00:22:20,840 --> 00:22:22,760
This isn't your business. Go to the car.

308
00:22:22,840 --> 00:22:23,760
Yes.

309
00:22:31,840 --> 00:22:34,080
Puna, I'll excuse myself now.

310
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:35,960
I have to go.

311
00:22:36,560 --> 00:22:37,520
Okay.

312
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:39,400
See you later.

313
00:22:52,920 --> 00:22:55,440
HT 2255 BANGKOK

314
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:00,320
Wait.

315
00:23:01,360 --> 00:23:03,640
-The delivery van already left?
-Yes.

316
00:23:10,040 --> 00:23:12,200
Is there anything I can help with?

317
00:23:13,360 --> 00:23:15,080
I was going to send this one
to be cleaned too.

318
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:19,600
I can take it to get washed.

319
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:22,920
I'll take it instead.

320
00:23:25,360 --> 00:23:26,960
I just got a new car,

321
00:23:27,040 --> 00:23:29,960
so I'll drive it to the laundry myself.

322
00:23:30,040 --> 00:23:33,360
I think I should do it.

323
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:36,480
I can clean it. It's just a little.
No need to send it to the shop.

324
00:23:36,560 --> 00:23:38,200
Spend your time on something else.

325
00:23:39,440 --> 00:23:42,360
Let Maria take it to the laundry.
You know the place, right?

326
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:45,680
Yes, I do. I'll take care of it myself.

327
00:23:49,920 --> 00:23:50,760
Maria.

328
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:53,600
I'll take it to the laundry for you.

329
00:23:53,680 --> 00:23:55,000
No need.

330
00:23:55,080 --> 00:23:58,120
I promised Mr. Singha
I'd handle it myself.

331
00:23:58,200 --> 00:24:00,760
-But I want to help.
-No!

332
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:03,840
-I really want to help.
-No!

333
00:24:03,920 --> 00:24:05,440
-What's going on?
-Oh!

334
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:07,760
Why are you interfering, Puna?

335
00:24:08,920 --> 00:24:11,400
Miss Maria, let's go for a drive.

336
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:12,840
Good idea.

337
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:18,640
We'll go for a drive. You stay here.

338
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:22,880
Teacher.

339
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:25,160
What should we do? Maria took the bear.

340
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:26,800
Let's follow her to the laundry.

341
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:29,240
Let's go.

342
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:38,040
All done. I've written down
all the medication instructions.

343
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:39,440
Make sure you take everything,

344
00:24:39,520 --> 00:24:41,280
or the infection could become resistant.

345
00:24:42,120 --> 00:24:43,240
Thanks, Doctor.

346
00:24:44,960 --> 00:24:46,160
Give the money to him.

347
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:05,040
Khod.

348
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:07,360
How did you get out?

349
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:09,880
The court granted me bail, Boss.

350
00:25:10,640 --> 00:25:13,400
For your case? They actually let you out?

351
00:25:14,520 --> 00:25:17,000
My brother-in-law's a lawyer,
so he handled it.

352
00:25:17,080 --> 00:25:18,760
Did you tell the police anything?

353
00:25:19,480 --> 00:25:21,880
Didn't tell them a thing.
We're on the same side.

354
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:24,920
How could I snitch on you or Pleaw?

355
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:27,600
If you aren't comfortable,

356
00:25:27,680 --> 00:25:30,920
let him rest for now.
Don't put him to work yet.

357
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:38,160
We're short on people anyway.
It's good to have Khod helping.

358
00:25:38,680 --> 00:25:40,000
Thank you, Boss.

359
00:25:42,360 --> 00:25:43,800
The car's ready, Boss.

360
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:46,400
Where are you going?

361
00:25:50,040 --> 00:25:51,920
Somewhere quiet to rest a bit.

362
00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:55,000
After I recover, I'll deal with them.

363
00:26:06,960 --> 00:26:11,600
LAUNDRY SERVICE

364
00:26:25,360 --> 00:26:27,480
LAUNDRY SERVICE

365
00:26:29,280 --> 00:26:31,640
This is the place.
Our company uses it regularly.

366
00:26:31,720 --> 00:26:32,600
Hey.

367
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:35,720
You need to check quickly.
If the bear goes in the machine,

368
00:26:35,800 --> 00:26:37,480
what's inside might get damaged.

369
00:26:37,560 --> 00:26:38,760
Yes.

370
00:26:38,840 --> 00:26:39,840
Excuse me.

371
00:26:41,080 --> 00:26:45,600
I'm not sure if Sophie
brought the teddy bear here for cleaning?

372
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:47,560
It's in the machine. Being washed now.

373
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:48,560
-What?
-What?

374
00:26:49,280 --> 00:26:50,320
No!

375
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:57,080
Is this the one?

376
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:05,440
Oh! Yes! That's it!

377
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:08,600
Hey!

378
00:27:08,680 --> 00:27:10,880
Quick, check inside! Hurry up.

379
00:27:17,680 --> 00:27:18,800
Found it?

380
00:27:20,040 --> 00:27:21,560
There's nothing inside.

381
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:24,160
What?

382
00:27:24,240 --> 00:27:25,400
Hey!

383
00:27:25,480 --> 00:27:26,760
No way.

384
00:27:26,840 --> 00:27:28,160
How is this possible?

385
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:41,280
The bow's a different color.

386
00:27:42,360 --> 00:27:45,360
-Could it be a different bear, Teacher?
-Yeah.

387
00:27:46,080 --> 00:27:48,440
I'll take a photo
and send it to Aunt Wilai first.

388
00:27:57,800 --> 00:27:58,640
She replied!

389
00:27:58,720 --> 00:27:59,600
What did she say?

390
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:00,720
IT'S A DIFFERENT ONE

391
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:01,880
It's a different one.

392
00:28:11,840 --> 00:28:14,040
Nothing wrong. Thank you very much.

393
00:28:14,720 --> 00:28:15,600
You're welcome.

394
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:21,280
Luckily,

395
00:28:21,360 --> 00:28:23,040
it was a different one.

396
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:25,480
Otherwise, the stuff inside
would have been ruined.

397
00:28:26,840 --> 00:28:28,920
So where's that teddy bear now?

398
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:31,400
It's in Mr. Singha's office.

399
00:28:34,800 --> 00:28:35,960
-Let's go.
-Okay.

400
00:28:57,280 --> 00:28:58,600
Hello? What is it?

401
00:28:58,680 --> 00:29:02,760
Someone from your company came
and checked something inside a bear.

402
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:05,120
Who?

403
00:29:05,200 --> 00:29:07,000
-Puna.
-Puna?

404
00:29:20,240 --> 00:29:23,360
Sorry, but I don't like anyone
messing with my teddy bear.

405
00:29:25,600 --> 00:29:27,200
Let me wash

406
00:29:27,280 --> 00:29:29,360
this teddy bear for you.

407
00:29:34,560 --> 00:29:35,600
Actually, never mind.

408
00:29:37,040 --> 00:29:37,960
You don't need to wash it.

409
00:29:46,240 --> 00:29:47,400
Mr. Singha.

410
00:29:47,920 --> 00:29:50,560
The plushies sent in,
should I handle it like before?

411
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:52,360
Yes.

412
00:29:52,880 --> 00:29:56,720
Put 20 kilos from this batch in,
separate the boxes.

413
00:29:56,800 --> 00:29:57,880
Got it.

414
00:30:08,400 --> 00:30:09,400
Puna.

415
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:17,440
Could she be a police informant?

416
00:30:22,160 --> 00:30:23,280
Chaiya.

417
00:30:23,360 --> 00:30:26,880
I saw the way Mr. Sonrak looks at Puna,
like he's hiding something.

418
00:30:27,400 --> 00:30:28,680
I know.

419
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:30,560
I think he's serious about her.

420
00:30:31,960 --> 00:30:32,920
I know that too.

421
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:35,360
Hey! I know! I know!

422
00:30:35,440 --> 00:30:38,160
Nothing else to say?
Should I snap you out of it?

423
00:30:39,400 --> 00:30:41,960
When I say I know, I mean

424
00:30:42,040 --> 00:30:45,680
I won't step aside for Sonrak,
not even one step.

425
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:50,000
But you'll step back if I say so.

426
00:30:50,760 --> 00:30:51,880
Here, take this!

427
00:31:50,880 --> 00:31:54,080
Hey, stuff 20 kilos of these
into the plushies,

428
00:31:54,160 --> 00:31:55,840
and pack them into boxes like before.

429
00:31:55,920 --> 00:31:57,160
Got it, Aew.

430
00:32:22,120 --> 00:32:23,360
The car's gone.

431
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:25,640
-Then let's head to the office.
-Okay.

432
00:32:25,720 --> 00:32:26,840
Let's go.

433
00:32:29,400 --> 00:32:30,400
Let's go.

434
00:32:33,600 --> 00:32:37,360
DARATHONG MUSIC

435
00:32:45,840 --> 00:32:47,120
Found it, Puna?

436
00:32:47,800 --> 00:32:49,040
No.

437
00:32:49,120 --> 00:32:51,480
I don't think the bear's
in this room anymore.

438
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:54,760
But I remember, it really was here before.

439
00:32:55,360 --> 00:32:56,560
Think carefully.

440
00:32:58,040 --> 00:32:58,960
Hey.

441
00:32:59,040 --> 00:33:00,680
Maybe it's in the props room.

442
00:33:01,920 --> 00:33:03,400
-Let's go check.
-Okay, let's go.

443
00:33:17,280 --> 00:33:18,160
Hey.

444
00:33:18,240 --> 00:33:20,600
Do you think it's in here, Puna?

445
00:33:20,680 --> 00:33:23,960
If it's not in the office,
it has to be in this room, Teacher.

446
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:25,240
Alright.

447
00:33:33,840 --> 00:33:36,160
These accessories
still look usable, Puna.

448
00:33:36,920 --> 00:33:38,560
-Wow.
-Yeah.

449
00:33:39,560 --> 00:33:41,120
They're all so pretty!

450
00:33:48,320 --> 00:33:51,960
DARATHONG MUSIC

451
00:35:12,440 --> 00:35:14,240
Has all our staff left yet?

452
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:18,600
The security said Puna
and Teacher Mueangphrai haven't left yet.

453
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:28,440
Found it yet, Teacher?

454
00:35:30,840 --> 00:35:31,760
Nothing here.

455
00:35:36,280 --> 00:35:37,600
I don't think it's in this room.

456
00:35:44,280 --> 00:35:45,640
Mr. Singha.

457
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:49,520
What are you two doing here?

458
00:35:56,800 --> 00:35:59,760
We came to look for accessories
to go with the outfits.

459
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:01,920
But earlier,

460
00:36:02,480 --> 00:36:05,640
the laundry staff called
and said you went there.

461
00:36:09,120 --> 00:36:10,200
Yes.

462
00:36:11,080 --> 00:36:12,320
The accessories

463
00:36:12,400 --> 00:36:15,720
had fallen off somewhere.
We saw someone took them to be washed,

464
00:36:15,800 --> 00:36:17,040
so we went there.

465
00:36:18,560 --> 00:36:19,640
That's right.

466
00:36:19,720 --> 00:36:22,440
But we didn't find anything,
so we came back to check here.

467
00:36:23,880 --> 00:36:24,720
Here.

468
00:36:27,240 --> 00:36:29,120
We did find some old accessories

469
00:36:29,200 --> 00:36:31,360
that can be used as replacements.

470
00:36:35,240 --> 00:36:36,240
Okay.

471
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:37,760
Good that you found something.

472
00:36:39,720 --> 00:36:40,880
You can leave now.

473
00:36:47,080 --> 00:36:48,520
That was close, Teacher.

474
00:36:48,600 --> 00:36:50,000
Yeah, indeed.

475
00:36:51,360 --> 00:36:54,040
Let's head back. We can continue tomorrow.

476
00:36:54,120 --> 00:36:55,160
Let's go.

477
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:54,840
<i>When will you accept</i>

478
00:37:55,920 --> 00:37:58,400
<i>When will you know</i>

479
00:37:59,120 --> 00:38:01,160
<i>If you already have a love</i>

480
00:38:01,680 --> 00:38:05,440
<i>Please hurry and tell me</i>

481
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:08,360
<i>If you're still single</i>

482
00:38:08,440 --> 00:38:12,120
<i>I beg you, with kindness</i>

483
00:38:12,200 --> 00:38:14,240
<i>Take a little time</i>

484
00:38:14,320 --> 00:38:19,240
<i>To consider my heart</i>

485
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:24,480
<i>I offer you my heart</i>
<i>Waiting for your answer</i>

486
00:38:29,960 --> 00:38:33,720
I've told you so many times not to come!
Why won't you listen?

487
00:38:33,800 --> 00:38:36,200
You know I'm famous right now.

488
00:38:36,720 --> 00:38:38,960
I can't let anyone know
I already have a family.

489
00:38:40,600 --> 00:38:43,000
But our son and I miss you.

490
00:38:50,440 --> 00:38:51,840
I miss you and our son too.

491
00:38:52,880 --> 00:38:54,200
But you have to understand me.

492
00:38:56,360 --> 00:38:59,600
I brought Sonrak with me.
He is asleep at the temple hall.

493
00:39:00,200 --> 00:39:02,400
Could you stop by
and see him for a moment?

494
00:39:02,480 --> 00:39:03,600
I can't.

495
00:39:03,680 --> 00:39:08,000
If anyone sees me, it's over.
We can't meet.

496
00:39:08,080 --> 00:39:10,560
Then I'll give you this teddy bear.

497
00:39:10,640 --> 00:39:14,480
And please, make sure
to read our son's letter.

498
00:39:21,680 --> 00:39:22,960
I'll send money.

499
00:39:24,040 --> 00:39:25,040
I have to go now.

500
00:39:25,640 --> 00:39:26,800
Yes.

501
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:39,720
I'll take the fan gift
and store it at the company.

502
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:57,320
DADDY, I MISS YOU SO MUCH

503
00:39:58,040 --> 00:40:01,200
<i>Daddy, I miss you so much.</i>

504
00:40:02,200 --> 00:40:04,800
<i>But Mommy says we can't see you yet,</i>

505
00:40:04,880 --> 00:40:07,400
<i>because you're working</i>
<i>to earn money for us.</i>

506
00:40:07,480 --> 00:40:11,960
<i>Daddy, Mommy is unwell</i>
<i>and can't go to work.</i>

507
00:40:12,040 --> 00:40:14,760
<i>I really want to see you. Sonrak.</i>

508
00:40:21,080 --> 00:40:22,560
I can't go see you yet, son.

509
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:35,920
Back then,

510
00:40:37,240 --> 00:40:38,960
if only I had taken better care of you…

511
00:40:42,960 --> 00:40:44,960
you wouldn't have left me so soon.

512
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:12,320
Dad.

513
00:41:15,520 --> 00:41:18,600
This is Mom's teddy bear, isn't it?

514
00:41:21,760 --> 00:41:22,960
Today is…

515
00:41:24,600 --> 00:41:26,480
the anniversary of her death.

516
00:41:27,880 --> 00:41:28,880
You remember?

517
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:30,520
I could never forget.

518
00:41:32,640 --> 00:41:34,280
I've regretted it every day.

519
00:41:36,400 --> 00:41:38,920
I couldn't be there with you and your mom.

520
00:41:40,960 --> 00:41:42,600
But you have to understand, Sonrak.

521
00:41:42,680 --> 00:41:44,520
If the truth got out

522
00:41:45,120 --> 00:41:46,680
that I had a family,

523
00:41:48,920 --> 00:41:51,160
it would ruin our future.

524
00:41:53,040 --> 00:41:55,480
I understand, Dad.

525
00:41:55,560 --> 00:41:58,680
Now that I'm a singer like you,
I understand even more.

526
00:41:58,760 --> 00:42:01,200
Fans are everything to us.

527
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:04,680
We have to do everything
to earn their support.

528
00:42:04,760 --> 00:42:06,880
They give us a living.

529
00:42:06,960 --> 00:42:09,680
We have to sacrifice our personal lives

530
00:42:10,200 --> 00:42:12,200
to make them happy.

531
00:42:12,800 --> 00:42:14,040
Poor thing.

532
00:42:14,560 --> 00:42:18,040
Your mom was a volunteer,
always helping everyone

533
00:42:18,120 --> 00:42:19,400
when the epidemic hit.

534
00:42:20,320 --> 00:42:21,520
That's right.

535
00:42:22,720 --> 00:42:26,000
She helped the villagers and ended up
catching tuberculosis herself.

536
00:42:26,080 --> 00:42:27,960
No one, Dad.

537
00:42:28,040 --> 00:42:31,520
No one cared about her at all.
She went to the villagers for help,

538
00:42:32,120 --> 00:42:34,160
and they ignored her completely.

539
00:42:34,760 --> 00:42:36,000
When she died,

540
00:42:36,080 --> 00:42:38,720
I was furious at those villagers
at how they treated her.

541
00:42:38,800 --> 00:42:40,400
It's all in the past.

542
00:42:42,200 --> 00:42:44,080
Mom's been gone for years now.

543
00:42:45,520 --> 00:42:46,840
Let's just move on from it.

544
00:42:51,640 --> 00:42:53,800
You really are your mother's son.

545
00:43:01,320 --> 00:43:04,080
This teddy bear, she gave it to me.

546
00:43:07,520 --> 00:43:09,000
Do you want to keep it in your room?

547
00:43:12,200 --> 00:43:13,600
Really, Dad?

548
00:43:14,640 --> 00:43:16,440
I miss Mom too.

549
00:43:25,160 --> 00:43:26,120
Thank you, Dad.

550
00:43:43,920 --> 00:43:44,880
Everyone.

551
00:43:46,120 --> 00:43:47,440
I want to show you something.

552
00:43:53,720 --> 00:43:56,360
This is my teddy bear.
It's a little stand-in for my mom.

553
00:43:59,760 --> 00:44:01,880
I miss her so much, everyone.

554
00:44:21,600 --> 00:44:22,720
Good night.

555
00:44:42,640 --> 00:44:44,920
Oh! Wow!

556
00:44:50,440 --> 00:44:52,120
Too bad Wilai isn't here.

557
00:44:52,640 --> 00:44:54,280
She'd get to see the my dance moves.

558
00:44:55,360 --> 00:44:58,680
Lucky her! No nightmares for her!

559
00:44:59,280 --> 00:45:01,120
You've got a sharp tongue, Puna.

560
00:45:01,200 --> 00:45:03,760
-I'm just kidding. Just joking!
-Alright.

561
00:45:10,400 --> 00:45:11,280
Teacher!

562
00:45:12,280 --> 00:45:13,400
-Look at this!
-What?

563
00:45:20,000 --> 00:45:23,080
Don't tell me that bear
ended up with Sonrak?

564
00:45:24,560 --> 00:45:25,640
I think so.

565
00:45:26,160 --> 00:45:28,520
I remember this one for sure.

566
00:45:29,040 --> 00:45:29,960
Our target

567
00:45:30,040 --> 00:45:32,440
just changed locations to his house.

568
00:45:32,520 --> 00:45:33,800
This is gonna be tough.

569
00:45:35,160 --> 00:45:36,560
What should we do?

570
00:45:37,080 --> 00:45:39,320
How can we find a reason
to go to his place?

571
00:45:41,480 --> 00:45:43,120
Just go be his girlfriend.

572
00:45:44,960 --> 00:45:46,200
Forget the house.

573
00:45:46,280 --> 00:45:49,240
You can even get
into that teddy bear's room.

574
00:45:50,480 --> 00:45:51,440
-A girlfriend?
-Yeah.

575
00:45:59,880 --> 00:46:01,160
Is that Chaiya's voice?

576
00:46:01,240 --> 00:46:05,120
CHAIYA

577
00:46:05,200 --> 00:46:07,360
Yeah, that's him singing.

578
00:46:08,040 --> 00:46:10,200
I set it as my ringtone.

579
00:46:14,560 --> 00:46:15,520
Hello?

580
00:46:17,800 --> 00:46:20,600
Did you get a chance
to listen to the recording I sent?

581
00:46:20,680 --> 00:46:21,720
Yes, I did.

582
00:46:22,680 --> 00:46:24,160
How is it? Was it okay?

583
00:46:24,240 --> 00:46:25,360
It's great!

584
00:46:25,440 --> 00:46:28,040
So good that I set it as my ringtone.

585
00:46:30,520 --> 00:46:31,600
<i>Don't, Teacher.</i>

586
00:46:31,680 --> 00:46:33,240
I'm embarrassed!

587
00:46:33,320 --> 00:46:35,440
Embarrassed? Your voice is amazing.

588
00:46:35,960 --> 00:46:38,040
Don't worry. If no one asks,

589
00:46:38,120 --> 00:46:41,840
I won't tell anyone who sang it.

590
00:46:43,400 --> 00:46:45,800
And Teacher,

591
00:46:47,920 --> 00:46:50,280
please don't let Puna find out.

592
00:46:51,280 --> 00:46:53,360
I'm shy.

593
00:46:54,520 --> 00:46:55,680
Too late!

594
00:46:57,000 --> 00:46:59,080
I heard it loud and clear!

595
00:46:59,160 --> 00:47:02,000
Alright, that's it for now. When we meet,

596
00:47:02,720 --> 00:47:04,800
we'll talk about your singing.

597
00:47:05,880 --> 00:47:06,800
Okay.

598
00:47:15,600 --> 00:47:17,560
I have to figure out a way

599
00:47:17,640 --> 00:47:21,120
to get that teddy bear
from Sonrak's house.

600
00:47:31,080 --> 00:47:32,680
Here, take one.

601
00:47:32,760 --> 00:47:33,760
Hey, whoa!

602
00:47:34,360 --> 00:47:35,320
It's a bomb, Chart!

603
00:47:35,400 --> 00:47:38,560
NEXT EPISODE

604
00:47:38,640 --> 00:47:40,680
On, tell me.

605
00:47:42,040 --> 00:47:43,960
What secret did you find out?

606
00:47:44,040 --> 00:47:45,400
What are you looking for?

607
00:47:46,400 --> 00:47:48,960
Is it the guy who walks with a limp?

608
00:47:51,760 --> 00:47:54,080
Here they are!
The old plushies and its old clothes.

609
00:47:54,160 --> 00:47:55,680
This car is carrying drugs.

610
00:47:56,840 --> 00:47:57,840
-Drugs?
-Drugs?

611
00:50:57,000 --> 00:51:02,200
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
